A security expert and former Commissioner of Police Federal Capital Territory FCT, Compol Lawrence Alobi says the fight against insecurity has gone beyond the security agencies stressing that depending on security agencies alone is a risk. Alobi made the remarks while delivering a speech at the security summit which rounded off in Calabar.
The former police chief maintained that security agents alone cannot combat the war against Boko Haram, militancy, kidnapping, rape and cultism.
Alobi stated that a time has come when every hand has to be on deck by providing useful information, by carrying out surveillance and being security conscious’. In his words, Alobi said, fight against insecurity in the country has gone beyond the security agencies depending on them is a risk”. The event which drew participants from academic world, other security experts, security operatives, traditional rulers, clergymen and students union leaders suggested that more should by the people, including corporate entities to combat crime at the state/ federal level. The participants suggested for the installation of security cameras at strategic points in the state and in most towns of the federation so as to help security operatives in tracking those perpetrating criminal activities in the nation and indeed the state capital. The participants said it is by so doing that the spate of insecurity can be arrested by security agents for sustenance of peace and tranquillity on the state.